line.comment: * Check if we can use Jumpdrive during general navigation
* Object to resupply was not found in this sector or fuel resupply is not needed
*= [THIS]-> call script 'wwsl.T2.function' : fn=594 arg1=': DEBUG-nav.move check sector %s to refueler' arg2=$tSector.Curr arg3=null arg4=null arg5=null
* Additional rules to break just to be sure
*= [THIS]-> call script 'wwsl.T2.function' : fn=594 arg1=': DEBUG-nav.move to jump to %s needed=%s available=%s' arg2=$tSector.Curr arg3=$x arg4=$JD.Available.Fuel arg5=null
* We was unable to jump directly to target
* Try to jump to a most farthest sector on route
* At least one jumpable gate in this sector
* If the target is docked (means the target is a ship)
* TODO: Required processing of the docked targets
* No refuel on route? Just jump as far as possible.
* It will work in this version.
* Again: we cannot ignore orbital accelerators
* Should use our smart jumping procedure.
* No gate? It's strange. Just move.
* We can be in refuel sector or not.
* No guaranties. Just return on this.
* We're in refueling sector. Dock with nearest refueling dept.
* X3AP: We cannot jump and forget of orbital accelerator anymore
* This call will return FLRET_ERROR and we will stuck forever.
* We should try to jump to all gates on route until success.
* Or fly to next sector as usual on failure.
